headline: HUM Q2 Deep Dive: Pharmacy Strength, Medicaid Expansion, and Guidance Lift
summary: Health insurance company Humana (NYSE:HUM) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 9.6% year on year to $32.39 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $128 billion at the midpoint came in 1% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $6.27 per share was 6.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
